OL,3,CProtection demanded for 'toilet bowl'
OL,4,Charbour water in Christchurch
OL,6,FEnvironmental campaigners who describe
OL,7,FChristchurch Harbour as the 'toilet
OL,8,Fbowl' of Bournemouth are demanding
OL,9,Fmore protection for the area.
OL,11,FTesting over the past two years shows
OL,12,Fa high level of pollution and now a
OL,13,Fpetition, to get the same protected
OL,14,Fstatus as Poole Harbour, has gained
OL,15,Fmore than 1,000 signatures.
OL,17,FUnlike other enclosed harbours in the
OL,18,FSouth such as Poole, Portsmouth and
OL,19,FChichester, Christchurch has not one,
OL,20,Fbut two large rivers draining into it
OL,21,F- the Stour and the Avon.
